Options.Documentation: Name of the resource group to which the resource belongs.

Options.Name: cluster_name
Options.Documentation: The name of the cluster within the specified resource group. Cluster names can only contain a combination of alphanumeric characters along with dash (-) and underscore (_). The name must be from 1 through 64 characters long.

Options.Name: parameters
Options.Documentation: The parameters to provide for cluster creation.

Options.Name: location
Options.Documentation: Resource location. If not set, location from the resource group will be used as default.

Options.Name: vm_size
Options.Documentation: All virtual machines in a cluster are the same size. For information about available VM sizes for clusters using images from the Virtual Machines Marketplace (see Sizes for Virtual Machines (Linux) or Sizes for Virtual Machines (Windows). Batch AI service supports all Azure VM sizes except STANDARD_A0 and those with premium storage (STANDARD_GS, STANDARD_DS, and STANDARD_DSV2 series).

Options.Name: vm_priority
Options.Documentation: Default is dedicated.

SubOptions.Name: target_node_count
SubOptions.Documentation: Default is 0. If autoScaleSettings are not specified, then the Cluster starts with this target.

SubOptions.Name: node_deallocation_option
SubOptions.Documentation: The default value is requeue.

SubOptions.Name: std_out_err_path_prefix
SubOptions.Documentation: The path where the Batch AI service will upload the stdout and stderror of setup task.

SubOptions.Name: azure_file_shares
SubOptions.Documentation: References to Azure File Shares that are to be mounted to the cluster nodes.

SubOptions.Name: account_key
SubOptions.Documentation: One of accountKey or accountKeySecretReference must be specified.

SubOptions.Name: account_key_secret_reference
SubOptions.Documentation: Users can store their secrets in Azure KeyVault and pass it to the Batch AI Service to integrate with KeyVault. One of accountKey or accountKeySecretReference must be specified.

SubOptions.Name: relative_mount_path
SubOptions.Documentation: Note that all file shares will be mounted under $AZ_BATCHAI_MOUNT_ROOT location.

SubOptions.Name: file_mode
SubOptions.Documentation: Default value is 0777. Valid only if OS is linux.

SubOptions.Documentation: Default value is 0777. Valid only if OS is linux.

ResponseFields.Name: provisioning_state
ResponseFields.Description: Possible value are: creating - Specifies that the cluster is being created. succeeded - Specifies that the cluster has been created successfully. failed - Specifies that the cluster creation has failed. deleting - Specifies that the cluster is being deleted. Possible values include: 'creating', 'succeeded', 'failed', 'deleting'

ResponseFields.Name: allocation_state
ResponseFields.Description: Possible values are: steady and resizing. steady state indicates that the cluster is not resizing. There are no changes to the number of compute nodes in the cluster in progress. A cluster enters this state when it is created and when no operations are being performed on the cluster to change the number of compute nodes. resizing state indicates that the cluster is resizing; that is, compute nodes are being added to or removed from the cluster. Possible values include: 'steady', 'resizing'

ResponseFields.Name: errors
ResponseFields.Description: This element contains all the errors encountered by various compute nodes during node setup.

SubFields.Name: code
SubFields.Description: An identifier for the error. Codes are invariant and are intended to be consumed programmatically.

SubFields.Name: message
SubFields.Description: A message describing the error, intended to be suitable for display in a user interface.

SubFields.Name: details
SubFields.Description: A list of additional details about the error.

Options.Name: resource_group_name
Options.Documentation: Name of the resource group to which the resource belongs.

Options.Name: job_name
Options.Documentation: The name of the job within the specified resource group. Job names can only contain a combination of alphanumeric characters along with dash (-) and underscore (_). The name must be from 1 through 64 characters long.

Options.Name: parameters
Options.Documentation: The parameters to provide for job creation.

Options.Name: location
Options.Documentation: Resource location. If not set, location from the resource group will be used as default.

Options.Name: experiment_name
Options.Documentation: Describe the experiment information of the job

Options.Name: priority
Options.Documentation: Priority associated with the job. Priority values can range from -1000 to 1000, with -1000 being the lowest priority and 1000 being the highest priority. The default value is 0.

SubOptions.Name: id
SubOptions.Documentation: The ID of the resource

Options.Name: node_count
Options.Documentation: The job will be gang scheduled on that many compute nodes

Options.Name: container_settings
Options.Documentation: If the container was downloaded as part of cluster setup then the same container image will be used. If not provided, the job will run on the VM.

SubOptions.Name: password
SubOptions.Documentation: One of password or passwordSecretReference must be specified.

SubOptions.Name: password_secret_reference
SubOptions.Documentation: Users can store their secrets in Azure KeyVault and pass it to the Batch AI Service to integrate with KeyVault. One of password or passwordSecretReference must be specified.

SubOptions.Name: language_type
SubOptions.Documentation: Valid values are 'BrainScript' or 'Python'.

SubOptions.Name: config_file_path
SubOptions.Documentation: This property can be specified only if the languageType is 'BrainScript'.

SubOptions.Name: python_script_file_path
SubOptions.Documentation: This property can be specified only if the languageType is 'Python'.

SubOptions.Name: python_interpreter_path
SubOptions.Documentation: This property can be specified only if the languageType is 'Python'.

SubOptions.Name: process_count
SubOptions.Documentation: The default value for this property is equal to nodeCount property

SubOptions.Name: worker_command_line_args
SubOptions.Documentation: This property is optional for single machine training.

SubOptions.Name: parameter_server_command_line_args
SubOptions.Documentation: This property is optional for single machine training.

SubOptions.Name: worker_count
SubOptions.Documentation: If specified, the value must be less than or equal to (nodeCount * numberOfGPUs per VM). If not specified, the default value is equal to nodeCount. This property can be specified only for distributed TensorFlow training

SubOptions.Name: parameter_server_count
SubOptions.Documentation: If specified, the value must be less than or equal to nodeCount. If not specified, the default value is equal to 1 for distributed TensorFlow training (This property is not applicable for single machine training). This property can be specified only for distributed TensorFlow training.

SubOptions.Name: config_file_path
SubOptions.Documentation: This property cannot be specified if pythonScriptFilePath is specified.

SubOptions.Name: python_script_file_path
SubOptions.Documentation: This property cannot be specified if configFilePath is specified.

SubOptions.Name: python_interpreter_path
SubOptions.Documentation: This property can be specified only if the pythonScriptFilePath is specified.

SubOptions.Name: process_count
SubOptions.Documentation: The default value for this property is equal to nodeCount property

SubOptions.Name: process_count
SubOptions.Documentation: The default value for this property is equal to nodeCount property

Options.Name: job_preparation
Options.Documentation: The specified actions will run on all the nodes that are part of the job

SubOptions.Name: command_line
SubOptions.Documentation: If containerSettings is specified on the job, this commandLine will be executed in the same container as job. Otherwise it will be executed on the node.

Options.Name: std_out_err_path_prefix
Options.Documentation: The path where the Batch AI service will upload stdout and stderror of the job.

SubOptions.Name: id
SubOptions.Documentation: It will be available for the job as an environment variable under AZ_BATCHAI_INPUT_id. The service will also provide the following  environment variable: AZ_BATCHAI_PREV_OUTPUT_Name. The value of the variable will be populated if the job is being retried after a previous failure, otherwise it will be set to nothing.

SubOptions.Name: id
SubOptions.Documentation: It will be available for the job as an environment variable under AZ_BATCHAI_OUTPUT_id.

SubOptions.Name: path_prefix
SubOptions.Documentation: NOTE: This is an absolute path to prefix. E.g. $AZ_BATCHAI_MOUNT_ROOT/MyNFS/MyLogs.

SubOptions.Name: path_suffix
SubOptions.Documentation: The suffix path where the output directory will be created.

SubOptions.Name: type
SubOptions.Documentation: Default value is Custom. The possible values are Model, Logs, Summary, and Custom. Users can use multiple enums for a single directory. Eg. outPutType='Model,Logs, Summary'.

SubOptions.Name: create_new
SubOptions.Documentation: Default is true. If false, then the directory is not created and can be any directory path that the user specifies.

Options.Name: environment_variables
Options.Documentation: Batch AI service sets the following environment variables for all jobs: AZ_BATCHAI_INPUT_id, AZ_BATCHAI_OUTPUT_id, AZ_BATCHAI_NUM_GPUS_PER_NODE. For distributed TensorFlow jobs, following additional environment variables are set by the Batch AI Service: AZ_BATCHAI_PS_HOSTS, AZ_BATCHAI_WORKER_HOSTS

Options.Name: constraints
Options.Documentation: Constraints associated with the Job.

SubOptions.Name: max_wall_clock_time
SubOptions.Documentation: Default Value = 1 week.

ResponseFields.Name: provisioning_state
ResponseFields.Description: The provisioned state of the Batch AI job. Possible values include: 'creating', 'succeeded', 'failed', 'deleting'

ResponseFields.Name: provisioning_state_transition_time
ResponseFields.Description: The time at which the job entered its current provisioning state.

ResponseFields.Name: execution_state
ResponseFields.Description: The current state of the job. Possible values are: queued - The job is queued and able to run. A job enters this state when it is created, or when it is awaiting a retry after a failed run. running - The job is running on a compute cluster. This includes job-level preparation such as downloading resource files or set up container specified on the job - it does not necessarily mean that the job command line has started executing. terminating - The job is terminated by the user, the terminate operation is in progress. succeeded - The job has completed running succesfully and exited with exit code 0. failed - The job has finished unsuccessfully (failed with a non-zero exit code) and has exhausted its retry limit. A job is also marked as failed if an error occurred launching the job. Possible values include: 'queued', 'running', 'terminating', 'succeeded', 'failed'

ResponseFields.Name: execution_state_transition_time
ResponseFields.Description: The time at which the job entered its current execution state.

ResponseFields.Name: execution_info
ResponseFields.Description: Contains information about the execution of a job in the Azure Batch service.

SubFields.Name: start_time
SubFields.Description: 'Running' corresponds to the running state. If the job has been restarted or retried, this is the most recent time at which the job started running. This property is present only for job that are in the running or completed state.

SubFields.Name: end_time
SubFields.Description: This property is only returned if the job is in completed state.

SubFields.Name: exit_code
SubFields.Description: This property is only returned if the job is in completed state.

SubFields.Name: parameter_server_count
SubFields.Description: If specified, the value must be less than or equal to nodeCount. If not specified, the default value is equal to 1 for distributed TensorFlow training (This property is not applicable for single machine training). This property can be specified only for distributed TensorFlow training.

SubFields.Name: config_file_path
SubFields.Description: This property cannot be specified if pythonScriptFilePath is specified.

SubFields.Name: python_script_file_path
SubFields.Description: This property cannot be specified if configFilePath is specified.

SubFields.Name: python_interpreter_path
SubFields.Description: This property can be specified only if the pythonScriptFilePath is specified.

SubFields.Name: process_count
SubFields.Description: The default value for this property is equal to nodeCount property

SubFields.Name: process_count
SubFields.Description: The default value for this property is equal to nodeCount property

ResponseFields.Name: job_preparation
ResponseFields.Description: The specified actions will run on all the nodes that are part of the job

SubFields.Name: command_line
SubFields.Description: If containerSettings is specified on the job, this commandLine will be executed in the same container as job. Otherwise it will be executed on the node.

ResponseFields.Name: std_out_err_path_prefix
ResponseFields.Description: The path where the Batch AI service will upload stdout and stderror of the job.

SubFields.Name: id
SubFields.Description: It will be available for the job as an environment variable under AZ_BATCHAI_INPUT_id. The service will also provide the following  environment variable: AZ_BATCHAI_PREV_OUTPUT_Name. The value of the variable will be populated if the job is being retried after a previous failure, otherwise it will be set to nothing.

SubFields.Name: id
SubFields.Description: It will be available for the job as an environment variable under AZ_BATCHAI_OUTPUT_id.

SubFields.Name: path_prefix
SubFields.Description: NOTE: This is an absolute path to prefix. E.g. $AZ_BATCHAI_MOUNT_ROOT/MyNFS/MyLogs.

SubFields.Name: path_suffix
SubFields.Description: The suffix path where the output directory will be created.

SubFields.Name: type
SubFields.Description: Default value is Custom. The possible values are Model, Logs, Summary, and Custom. Users can use multiple enums for a single directory. Eg. outPutType='Model,Logs, Summary'. Possible values include: 'model', 'logs', 'summary', 'custom'

SubFields.Name: create_new
SubFields.Description: Default is true. If false, then the directory is not created and can be any directory path that the user specifies.

ResponseFields.Name: environment_variables
ResponseFields.Description: Batch AI services sets the following environment variables for all jobs: AZ_BATCHAI_INPUT_id, AZ_BATCHAI_OUTPUT_id, AZ_BATCHAI_NUM_GPUS_PER_NODE, For distributed TensorFlow jobs, following additional environment variables are set by the Batch AI Service: AZ_BATCHAI_PS_HOSTS, AZ_BATCHAI_WORKER_HOSTS.

ResponseFields.Name: constraints
ResponseFields.Description: Constraints associated with the Job.

SubFields.Name: max_wall_clock_time
SubFields.Description: Default Value = 1 week.

ResponseFields.Name: creation_time
ResponseFields.Description: The creation time of the job.

ResponseFields.Name: provisioning_state
ResponseFields.Description: The provisioned state of the Batch AI job. Possible values include: 'creating', 'succeeded', 'failed', 'deleting'

ResponseFields.Name: provisioning_state_transition_time
ResponseFields.Description: The time at which the job entered its current provisioning state.

ResponseFields.Name: execution_state
ResponseFields.Description: The current state of the job. Possible values are: queued - The job is queued and able to run. A job enters this state when it is created, or when it is awaiting a retry after a failed run. running - The job is running on a compute cluster. This includes job-level preparation such as downloading resource files or set up container specified on the job - it does not necessarily mean that the job command line has started executing. terminating - The job is terminated by the user, the terminate operation is in progress. succeeded - The job has completed running succesfully and exited with exit code 0. failed - The job has finished unsuccessfully (failed with a non-zero exit code) and has exhausted its retry limit. A job is also marked as failed if an error occurred launching the job. Possible values include: 'queued', 'running', 'terminating', 'succeeded', 'failed'

ResponseFields.Name: execution_state_transition_time
ResponseFields.Description: The time at which the job entered its current execution state.

ResponseFields.Name: execution_info
ResponseFields.Description: Contains information about the execution of a job in the Azure Batch service.

SubFields.Name: start_time
SubFields.Description: 'Running' corresponds to the running state. If the job has been restarted or retried, this is the most recent time at which the job started running. This property is present only for job that are in the running or completed state.

SubFields.Name: end_time
SubFields.Description: This property is only returned if the job is in completed state.

SubFields.Name: exit_code
SubFields.Description: This property is only returned if the job is in completed state.

SubFields.Name: code
SubFields.Description: An identifier for the error. Codes are invariant and are intended to be consumed programmatically.

SubFields.Name: message
SubFields.Description: A message describing the error, intended to be suitable for display in a user interface.

SubFields.Name: details
SubFields.Description: A list of additional details about the error.
